-- Harmony Resumes Mining at Most of Its Phakisa Mine After a Fatal Explosion
-- Ron Derby
-- 2010-07-01T06:55:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/harmony-resumes-mining-at-most-of-its-phakisa-mine-after-a-fatal-explosion.html

          
          
             Harmony Gold Mining Ltd. said it
resumed operations at its Phakisa mine in South Africa apart
from at four sections which were affected by an explosion on
June 24, which killed four workers.  
 Investigations into the incident are continuing, Harmony
spokeswoman Esha Brijmohan said in an e-mailed response to
questions today. The mine produced 955 kilograms of gold in the
three months through March.  
